The healthcare facility has recently been re-opened after it was closed for three months to undergo renovations to the tune of a R1 million. JOHANNESBURG – The City of Cape Town says security measures have been beefed up at the newly renovated Hanover Park clinic. The healthcare facility has recently been re-opened after it was closed for three months to undergo renovations to the tune of R1 million. The city’s Siyabulela Mamkeli says: “We make sure that we’ve security personnel that is strengthened in the facility to ensure that there’s no easy access to the facility.”